    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The overall credibility assessment for COU1 is Accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions at Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is judged acceptable given the standardised ASTM F1717 protocol, corroborating multi-laboratory experimental data, and the conservative acceptance bounds applied to the E/uval metric. All three QoIs satisfy both the <10% difference and E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criteria. The FEA modeling framework is considered credible for its intended use in supporting regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design. Project requirements as documented in the design history file are addressed throughout the credibility evidence package.",
